The paper deals with the optimization of image acquisition and distribution workflow using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of statistical traces and digital watermarks for provenance analysis, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
